1.title: welcome + structure of experiment
1.content:
Welcome to this study!

During this study we will ask questions about self-injury, which might be sensitive. Please, do not participate in this study if you are not willing to answer such questions.

This study consists of 2 parts.

Part 1 is taking place now and Part 2 will take place in 30 days. Please, only participate in this study if you are willing to complete both parts of the study.

Part 1:

  • Is taking place now
  • Will take 10 minutes to complete
  • Compensation: after you completed Part 1 of the study you will receive £1
  • Structure:
    1. First, we will ask you some demographical questions (i.e., about age en gender, no other questions about your personal identity will be asked)
    2. In the second phase of this study, you will complete a task in which you will categorize statements as fast as possible.
      This task will take 5 minutes.
    3. After finishing this task, we will ask you some questions about non suicidal self-injury behavior and mental health in general.

Part 2:

  • Will take place in 30 days
  • Will take 2 minutes to complete
  • Compensation: after you completed Part 2 of the study you will receive £1.25 (£0.25 for your time and £1 for completing both parts of the study).
  • During this part, we will ask you 1 question about self-injury
  • We will send you an invitation to participate in Part 2 of the study through the Prolific website, 30 days from now. Please set an alarm in your agenda 30 days from now to notify you to check the Prolific website.


On the next few pages you will first receive some information and practical guidelines about the study. We will also ask you to provide us with your informed consent before the start of the study.

Please note that you can quit the study at any time by closing the browser window. However, please be aware that this will end your participation. If you are certain that you want to quit because the study is causing you distress or because you encounter technical issues that force you to quit, you can still receive a partial reward proportionate to the time you actually spent on the study. If this occurs, please take the following steps:

  1. Return the study via the Prolific study page as quickly as possible (please do not submit unless you have completed the study and received a completion code).
  2. Send a message to the researcher via the Prolific study page, stating that you completed part of the study (this will ensure that the researcher knows you should receive a partial reward).

These instructions will remain available at the bottom of the page throughout the study.

Press the space bar to continue.

2.title: information experiment
2.content:
Information about the study

Overview and procedures. During the study we will ask personal questions about self-injury. You will also be asked to emit certain responses regarding this behavior using the keyboard. During this task, you will be asked to be as quick and accurate as possible. Please only participate if you have no problem with providing such personal information. You are expected to pay close attention throughout the experiment and to work as accurately as possible. When questions are being asked, you are expected to answer truthfully.

Risks and benefits. This study involves no more risk to your physical or psychological health beyond those encountered in the normal course of everyday life. Please note that participating in this study will not benefit your psychological health and is not an alternative to any form of psychological help.

Confidentiality. Any information obtained in this study will be kept strictly confidential and used solely for research purposes. We do not ask any identifying information (other than your Prolific ID code) and responses will be kept completely anonymous. Your anonymized data (i.e., Prolific ID codes will be removed from the data) will be posted to a public repository for other researchers to make use of (e.g., to replicate the results of this experiment).

Results. After this study has ended and the data have been processed, it is possible to receive a summary of the research results. If you want to do so, please contact the researcher via the ‘Contact researcher’ button on the Prolific experiment page (please note that it might take a few weeks before a study is completely finished and the data fully processed).

Your rights. Your decision to participate in this research is voluntary. You can withdraw from the study at any time without penalty. You do not have to answer any questions you do not want to.

Payment policy. If you complete the full study, you will receive full payment for your participation. If you decide to withdraw from the study before you have completed it (regardless of the reason why) you are entitled to a payment proportionate to the time you actually spent on the study (taking into account the hourly rate). Instructions on how you can receive this partial reward will be available throughout the study.

Questions/issues. If you have any questions or issues with this study or regarding the questions that were asked, please use the ‘Contact researcher’ button on the Prolific experiment page (please mention the study name). The researcher will respond as quickly as possible.

People sometimes tend to have the urge to harm themselves or have thoughts about harming themselves. If this is the case for you, we encourage you to contact someone who can help you cope with these thoughts and actions and with any stressful events that may have caused them.
If you have questions about this or wish to contact someone who can help you, you can click on one of these links: website 1 or website 2
These are websites that contain hotlines for different countries. Please note that the websites say ‘suicide’, but you can also get help with regard to (non-suicidal) self-injury. On most websites, you can contact someone through chat or by telephone. You can also make a personal face-to-face appointment. The websites also contain self-help guides. Please be safe, and consider contacting someone.
Please note that we will provide the links to these websites again at the end of the study

Press the space bar if you have read this information and if you are ready to continue

3.content:
PARTICIPANT CONSENT FORM
Project Title: NSSI study

I hereby declare that I, as a participant in a study by the Department of Experimental Clinical and Health Psychology at Ghent University:

  1. received the explanation of the nature of the questions and the tasks during this study, and that I was given the opportunity to obtain additional information;

  2. voluntarily participate in this scientific study;

  3. give the researchers permission to save, process and report my results anonymously;

  4. am aware of the possibility to end my participation in the study at any time without having to give any reason;

  5. know that not participating or ending my participation in the study has no negative consequences

  6. know that on request, I can get a summary of the research findings after the study has been completed and the results are known;

  7. give permission for my anonymous data to be used for further analysis by other researchers;

  8. know that UGent is the responsible unit with regard to personal data collected during the study. I know that the data protection officer can provide me with more information about the protection of my personal information. Contact: Hanne Elsen (privacy@ugent.be).

You must be 18 years of age or older to participate in this research study.

Name of the main researcher: Femke Cathelyn (femke.cathelyn@ugent.be)

5.title: guidelines
5.content:
Thank you!
Some guidelines before the experiment starts:

Make sure that you are conducting this study on a laptop or regular desktop computer and NOT on a smartphone or tablet. You will need a keyboard to complete this study.

Do not close this tab and do not do other things on your laptop while completing this study. It is important that you keep paying attention and that you complete the study without taking a break. That way, you help us make this study useful.

Please, click

  • on F11 for Windows and Linux or

  • on ⌘ + Ctrl + f for Mac

now and keep this screen in full-screen mode during the entire study.

Keep in mind that all of the data will be processed anonymously. We are obliged to protect your privacy, and nobody will ever be able to link the answers that you gave to your personal identity.
Therefore, please help us and be honest when answering all questions.

Press the space bar to continue.

10.title: Reinsurance privacy protection
10.content:
Well done, you finished the task!

In the final phase of the first part of this study, we will ask you some more questions. We will ask questions about your personal experience with non-suicidal self-injury, more specifically we will ask you questions about cutting behavior. We will also ask you some other questions regarding your mental health.

Please pay careful attention when answering these questions. Our study will only have value when every participant answers truthfully. Please help us fulfil our scientific goals and give an honest answer to all questions.
Keep in mind that all of the data will be processed anonymously. We are obliged to protect your privacy, and nobody will ever be able to link the answers that you gave to your personal identity.
Therefore, please help us and be honest when answering all questions.

Press the space bar to continue.

If you want or have to quit the study before completing it, please return the study and contact the researcher.

131.title: aIAT_block1_instructions
131.content:
Task instructions: part 3

On every trial of the task, you will see a statement in the middle of the screen. Your task is to assign that statement to 1 of the 2 possible categories.

Please respond AS QUICKLY AS POSSIBLE, while at the same time, trying not to make too many mistakes (some mistakes are OK).


The two categories in the first part of the task are:

I HAVE CUT MY SKIN ON PURPOSE BEFORE and I HAVE NEVER CUT MY SKIN ON PURPOSE

If the statement belongs to the I HAVE CUT MY SKIN ON PURPOSE BEFORE category, press the E key (left on the keyboard).

If the statement belongs to the I HAVE NEVER CUT MY SKIN ON PURPOSE category, press the I key (right on the keyboard).


Words at the top of the screen will indicate which key (left/right) you need to press.

Keep your fingers on the E and I keys at all times, in order to respond faster.

Avoid all distractions and pay attention. Try to answer as quickly as possible!

Press the space bar when you have your fingers on the E and I keys and are ready to start the task.

If you want or have to quit the study before completing it, please return the study and contact the researcher.
